	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In some case, even if the game doesn't support multi-core, windows will try to spread the load on all of them so I guess there is not much you can do at the moment.
<br />
<br />You could always try to launch the game, go in the task manager and set the processor affinity for the game to CPU1 and see what happens but I cannot guarantee any improvement. Try it and let us know how it affected the game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

